<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/67047018-cavak"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/67047018-cavak">Cavak</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s funny to me that you only mentioned the alt-right when <i>Adjustment Day</i> throws just as many barbs at the alt-left too. In fact, dozens of North Ame<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's funny to me that you only mentioned the alt-right when <i>Adjustment Day</i> throws just as many barbs at the alt-left too. In fact, dozens of North American political ideologies and identities get wrecked. Trying to pin "accuracy" or "impressions" on any side is self-defeating, and that's sort of the point of the entire novel.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
