        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3483853770" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3748108188224175414">this apolitical dumpster fire disguises itself as a satire of trump era political divisions. A satire mind you no one needs right now because we are already fucking living it. ranging from stereotypes of incel fedora nazis who just wanna get laid to queer gender studies academic Twitter lynch mobsters to fake news revolutionaries of all colors and orientations. If that sentence sounds appealing maybe you’d like the book. I did not hate the book because my snowflake millennial political orientati</span>
  <span id="freeText3748108188224175414" style="display:none">this apolitical dumpster fire disguises itself as a satire of trump era political divisions. A satire mind you no one needs right now because we are already fucking living it. ranging from stereotypes of incel fedora nazis who just wanna get laid to queer gender studies academic Twitter lynch mobsters to fake news revolutionaries of all colors and orientations. If that sentence sounds appealing maybe you’d like the book. I did not hate the book because my snowflake millennial political orientation found the book “offensive.” The building of this world was pretty engaging for most of the first third of book and then it plods along at a pace where even its flashes of brilliance are dimmed by my growing rage. I do not connect. I pleaded for the dumpster fire to be put out if only so I could at the end see if I was wrong. That maybe this book has something to offer other than a few decent vignettes and clever quotes. But it adds up to nothing. The book has nothing to say. I’m not having fun tonight.</span>
