        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2379901507" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14041954982354003794">Oof. This one pains me quite a bit to write because I am such a huge Palahniuk fan and have been since I was a teen. But this book.... I can’t handle how terrible it is, it almost physical pains me. This is so far from his best work that it almost feels like it’s not Palahniuk that wrote it, it can’t be from the same person, it just can’t. I tried really hard to like it and kept telling myself to keep reading and to give it a chance like I do with every book and that it could only get better. Bu</span>
  <span id="freeText14041954982354003794" style="display:none">Oof. This one pains me quite a bit to write because I am such a huge Palahniuk fan and have been since I was a teen. But this book.... I can’t handle how terrible it is, it almost physical pains me. This is so far from his best work that it almost feels like it’s not Palahniuk that wrote it, it can’t be from the same person, it just can’t. I tried really hard to like it and kept telling myself to keep reading and to give it a chance like I do with every book and that it could only get better. But it didn’t get better, it just got infinitely worse. I made it through to the end (somehow) but it was a rough go and I’m just left so disappointed in this book. </span>
