  <span id="freeText17856303770068064860" style="display:none">7 days and 316 pages after. The newest book of the author but one of the most confusing books of Palahniuk Ive ever read. Of course the lenguage didn't help too much. We have a couple of paragraphs for the people (as me) that love the sordid of his feelings.<br /><br />Here, in our dystopia we have 3 different sides: Caucasia (the whites), Blacktopia (the blacks), and Gaysia (the queers). In adjustment day will be explained how all begins, why and how will end.<br /><br />Palahniuk is not easy as it seems. In this case we have too much characters, a couple very repetitive others useless. But we have too much for only three beside stories. Also the narrative wasn't the best for me, it was confusing and exhausting. <br /><br />I didn't love it. That was an statement, I was expecting more darkness, more hate or xenophobia. Something was missing.<br /><br />It has a couple of funny winks, but not the enough. <br /><br />There will be a former review. And we have enough of Palahniuk... At least this year.</span>
